d more rewarding than ever. Straightforward illustrations of key tools and steps help make this book one-stop shopping for wine lovers, beer brewers, avid cooks, or anyone who’s ever dreamed of producing table wines at home. This updated and expanded edition features: * new how-to illustrations * tips and techniques from accomplished professional winemakers * up-to-date information on the rewards and challenges of running natural wine fermentations * fresh ways to apply your home-brewing knowledge to make remarkable reds and whites Providing concise, clear, and practical guidance, Sheridan Warrick shows that making your own wine is not only easy but also a pleasure.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aWine and wine makingvAmateurs' manuals. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aamateur vintner.  aamateur winemaker.  acalifornia wines.  aeasy wine at home.  afood and bev.  afood and wine.  ahome vineyards.  ahome vintners.  ahome winemaking.  ahome winery.  ahow to make wine.  amaking wine at home.  amaking your own wine.  aprofessional winemakers.  ared wine.  aviticulture.  awhite wine.  awine books.  awine lovers.  awine.  awinemaking equipment.  awinemaking for dummies.  awinemaking how to.  awinemaking instructions.  awinemaking schedule.  awinemaking step by step.  awinemaking.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028597240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096129640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961296423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961296/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d201